snippet: The Liberal Democratic Party was returned to power in parliamentary elections Sunday in what analysts say is more a vote against the incumbents than a mandate.
abstract: Japan’s voters hand a landslide victory to Liberal Democratic Party in national parliamentary elections, giving power back to conservative party that governed Japan for decades until historic defeat three years ago;  victory all but ensures that Liberal Democratic leader Shinzo Abe, former prime minister who is one Japan’s most outspoken nationalists, will be able to form new government.

byline.contributor: Makiko Inoue contributed reporting from Kawagoe, Japan.

lead_paragraph: The Liberal Democratic Party was returned to power in parliamentary elections Sunday in what analysts say is more a vote against the incumbents than a mandate.

headline.seo: Liberal Democratic Party Returns to Power in Japan
headline.main: Japan Election Returns Power to Old Guard
headline.print_headline: Japan Election Returns Power To Old Guard
